' Werke von AC/DC, Motörhead und Guns N'Roses mit ein.  aThe attraction of heavy metal has gone unbroken for 40 years. »Metal«, despite, or perhaps because of, its often ambivalent reputation, represents a global phenomenon, at the heart of which is a love of music.Dietmar Elflein deals intensively with heavy metal as music, and investigates LPs and bands that have shaped the genre, looking for musical commonalities and lines of development - the musical language of heavy metal. The diversity of the musical approaches investigated ranges from Black Sabbath through Judas Priest and Iron Maiden, right up to Metallica, Megadeth and Slayer, but also includes less 'metallic' works by AC/DC, Motörhead and Guns N' Roses.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Nov 2021) 4aHeavy Metal. 4aKlang. 4aKulturelles Gedächtnis. 4aMusik. 4aMusikalische Analyse. 4aMusikwissenschaft. 4aPopkultur. 4aPopmusik. 7aMUSIC / History & Criticism.2bisacsh  aMusic.  aMusicology.  aPop Music.  aSound.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Complete Package 2010-2013z9783110352856oZDB-23-TSO08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gruyterttranscript Highlight Collection Kunst Arch. 2010-2013z9783110370720oZDB-23-TKA40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/transcript.9783839415764zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783839415764423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783839415764/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA5EBK  aZDB-23-TKAc2010d2013  aZDB-23-TSOc2010d2013